WEBVTT

01:25.284 --> 01:28.288
♪♪

02:04.456 --> 02:06.159
[man on radio]
Ground control to David.

02:06.192 --> 02:09.362
Please provide a status update
on the meters.

02:09.395 --> 02:12.865
[David]
Um, I don't know
what the fuck I'm looking at?

02:12.898 --> 02:15.535
You know, I'm just
a maintenance technician, right?

02:15.568 --> 02:17.236
For the entire galaxy.

02:17.269 --> 02:20.840
You are categorized
as low-level maintenance crew.

02:20.873 --> 02:24.210
And when am I gonna get a--
an android up here?

02:26.345 --> 02:27.513
Are you feeling lonely?

02:27.546 --> 02:30.516
I'm alone.
I'm not lonely.

02:30.549 --> 02:33.452
Anyway, robots are
awful company.

02:33.485 --> 02:37.657
I just-- I don't like
these spacewalks.

02:37.690 --> 02:40.326
An android companion
is not an approved expense.

02:40.359 --> 02:43.329
Um, can you really
put a value on human life?

02:43.362 --> 02:46.532
You were registered
at a cost of $500,000.

02:46.565 --> 02:48.935
The android costs
$40 million.

02:48.968 --> 02:50.603
Please get us
those readings STAT.

02:50.636 --> 02:52.238
Humans on Earth
are not handling

02:52.271 --> 02:54.240
the recent surge
in thunderstorms well.

02:54.273 --> 02:57.443
Yeah, I got your readings
right here all right.

02:57.476 --> 03:01.314
- [automated voice] Warning!
- Mayday. Mayday, mayday!

03:01.347 --> 03:05.818
Warning! Warning!
Warning! Warning!

03:07.419 --> 03:10.223
Ground control,
what the hell
just happened?

03:10.256 --> 03:11.290
- Warning!
- Hey!

03:11.323 --> 03:12.491
Warning!

03:12.524 --> 03:16.395
Ground control,
can you hear me?
Hello!

03:16.428 --> 03:17.463
Hello!

03:17.496 --> 03:21.534
[sighs]
Christ!

03:21.567 --> 03:23.469
[thunder rumbles]

03:25.504 --> 03:27.273
[birds squawking]

03:42.521 --> 03:45.658
[Brian] A lot of them
are strays, or turned in
by owners

03:45.691 --> 03:47.793
who can't take care
of them anymore.

03:47.826 --> 03:51.030
[Olivia] I need one that has
some wine knowledge
and won't spill.

03:51.063 --> 03:53.332
My mom's
a bit particular.

03:53.365 --> 03:54.634
What about these two?

03:56.635 --> 03:58.638
This one is Charlie.

03:58.671 --> 04:01.274
He's a fully operational
companion robot.

04:01.307 --> 04:05.544
He served as an excellent
end of life caretaker
for elders.

04:05.577 --> 04:07.013
- He's great.
- Hm.

04:07.046 --> 04:11.651
- Is his outfit changeable?
- Yeah, sure, yeah.

04:11.684 --> 04:14.320
Do you want to get to know
Charlie in the meeting zone?

04:14.353 --> 04:15.822
Hm, okay, yeah.

04:22.528 --> 04:25.064
I'm super easygoing.

04:25.097 --> 04:28.901
[soft chuckle]
Comfortable with
any conversation topic.

04:28.934 --> 04:30.903
You can't shock me, hm?

04:32.671 --> 04:37.543
I can say "one more beer"
in over 48 languages.

04:37.576 --> 04:39.312
Take me on holiday.

04:39.345 --> 04:41.681
[chuckles] You're in
for a real treat.

04:41.714 --> 04:43.683
Can he clean pools?

04:43.716 --> 04:46.419
Actually, Charlie is
a little sensitive
with water.

04:46.452 --> 04:49.588
Oh, come on, Brian, I bet
you're no mermaid either.

04:49.621 --> 04:53.659
I am great at doing
the dead-man float.

04:53.692 --> 04:54.760
Am I right?

04:54.793 --> 04:57.663
Uh, no. Can I please
meet the other one?

04:57.696 --> 04:59.031
[Brian]
Let's take this outside.

04:59.064 --> 05:01.601
So, so, you like wine?

05:03.402 --> 05:04.770
Uh, my mom does.

05:04.803 --> 05:06.706
Okay, listen to this.

05:06.739 --> 05:10.643
What did the grape say
when it was being
stepped on?

05:10.676 --> 05:13.579
- Uh, I don't know?
- Nothing.

05:13.612 --> 05:15.715
He just let out
a little wine.

05:17.149 --> 05:18.851
Huh? Am I right?

05:18.884 --> 05:20.920
[chuckles]
Am I right?

05:20.953 --> 05:22.955
[indistinct chatter]

05:44.710 --> 05:48.914
- What did she say
about me, huh?
- It's a hard pass, Charlie.

05:48.947 --> 05:52.585
It was the dead-man float
shtick, huh?

05:52.618 --> 05:54.520
- A little too dark, wasn't I?
- [Brian chuckles]

05:54.553 --> 05:56.889
I don't think
she's your type of crowd.

05:56.922 --> 05:59.125
You weren't made
for young ones like that.

05:59.158 --> 06:01.494
I'm like a fine wine--

06:01.527 --> 06:04.029
- complex but very,
very fruity.
- Yeah.

06:04.062 --> 06:06.065
That should be
plenty enough walking.

06:06.098 --> 06:08.868
Okay,
it's bedtime, Charlie.

06:08.901 --> 06:11.103
I need to go
get some rest.

06:11.136 --> 06:12.972
Okay.

06:17.976 --> 06:20.146
[door whirs, beeps]

06:27.719 --> 06:29.956
Close your eyes, Charlie.

06:31.790 --> 06:34.427
- [indistinct TV chatter]
- [pills rattle]

07:01.019 --> 07:04.690
He can cook.
He makes amazing desserts.

07:04.723 --> 07:07.593
He's great
at small household tasks.

07:09.561 --> 07:12.631
No, no, he can't fix
electrical equipment.

07:12.664 --> 07:14.900
He's an older model,
he will fry.

07:14.933 --> 07:16.702
But he's amazing.

07:19.938 --> 07:21.507
No, I understand.

07:21.540 --> 07:23.742
We'll call you
if we get one of those.

07:23.775 --> 07:24.944
Yeah.

07:24.977 --> 07:27.947
I see here you said
to not call, my bad.

07:27.980 --> 07:29.549
Have a nice even--

07:30.983 --> 07:32.051
Asshole.

07:32.084 --> 07:34.720
[indistinct TV chatter]

07:37.122 --> 07:39.125
♪♪

07:45.197 --> 07:46.833
[David panting]

07:50.068 --> 07:52.571
Eva, engage thrusters.

07:52.604 --> 07:57.009
- [Eva] Thrusters damaged.
- Eva, engage thrusters.

07:57.042 --> 07:58.244
- Thrusters damaged.
- Eva?

07:59.678 --> 08:00.813
Ground control,
talk to me.

08:00.846 --> 08:02.114
[Eva] Connection stream
interrupted.

08:02.147 --> 08:03.248
[yells]

08:03.282 --> 08:05.217
- Connection stream
interrupted.
- [stammers]

08:05.250 --> 08:06.351
Repeat that, please.

08:06.385 --> 08:10.055
- Repeat.
- Lost connection
with com center.

08:10.088 --> 08:13.058
What do I do?
What's the protocol?

08:13.091 --> 08:15.594
Lost-lost-lost--
Lost connection--

08:15.627 --> 08:17.263
[yelling]

08:17.296 --> 08:19.231
Lost connection
with com center.

08:19.264 --> 08:21.600
- Sorry, repeat. Repeat--
- Lost connection
with com center.

08:21.633 --> 08:23.536
- Lost connection
with com center.
- Fuck.

08:23.569 --> 08:25.204
[thunder rumbles]

08:28.340 --> 08:31.544
♪♪

08:53.799 --> 08:56.235
- [chime]
- [God 2.0]
Good morning, Claire.

09:02.774 --> 09:06.845
Can I please have my daily
inspirational quote?

09:06.878 --> 09:09.715
Of course, Claire.
Today's inspiration is--

09:09.748 --> 09:11.216
"The best preparation
for tomorrow

09:11.249 --> 09:13.619
is doing your best today."

09:15.887 --> 09:17.256
I like that.

09:19.024 --> 09:20.659
Thank you, God.

09:20.692 --> 09:23.696
[rock music playing]

09:31.937 --> 09:34.106
[chiming]

09:34.139 --> 09:37.142
Claire,
I'm changing the music.

09:37.175 --> 09:39.912
This is not conducive
to spiritual growth.

09:39.945 --> 09:41.247
Okay, thank you.

09:42.681 --> 09:43.949
You're welcome.

09:43.982 --> 09:46.986
[soft music playing]

10:13.879 --> 10:16.315
[indistinct chatter on TV]

10:23.689 --> 10:25.924
[man on TV] Hi, my name is Chad.
I'm 24 years old,

10:25.957 --> 10:28.761
I love sports...

10:34.466 --> 10:36.068
[woman on TV]
Hi, I'm Lauren,

10:36.101 --> 10:38.738
and my best qualities
are not on the outside.

10:43.241 --> 10:44.844
Sinners.

10:45.678 --> 10:49.248
- I keep having bad thoughts.
- [chiming]

10:49.281 --> 10:51.283
And what are they, Clair?

10:51.316 --> 10:53.852
I feel envious of Sarah,
and so I keep fantasizing

10:53.885 --> 10:54.953
about her husband
cheating on her

10:54.986 --> 10:58.157
and then she has to come home
and she goes crazy.

10:58.190 --> 11:02.161
Envy is the art of counting
another's blessings
instead of your own.

11:04.996 --> 11:07.199
What are
my blessings, God?

11:09.000 --> 11:13.673
Um, my love for you,
and your wallpaper.

11:16.241 --> 11:17.877
[sighs heavily]

11:27.819 --> 11:29.755
[chiming]

11:30.756 --> 11:32.024
[engine starts]

11:41.767 --> 11:43.135
- [crashing]
- [chiming]

11:44.202 --> 11:46.405
Claire, I heard that.

11:46.438 --> 11:48.373
Uh, heard what?

11:48.406 --> 11:49.809
You hit a car.

11:50.909 --> 11:53.078
No, I didn't.

11:53.111 --> 11:54.079
[beeps]

11:54.112 --> 11:56.415
Lying. One sin recorded.

11:56.448 --> 11:58.984
How many sins
have I committed this month?

11:59.017 --> 12:02.421
You are at nine
venial sins this month.

12:02.454 --> 12:06.792
At ten sins,
you will be charged
$25.99 per venial sin.

12:08.493 --> 12:10.295
Can I just remove
the last sin?

12:10.328 --> 12:13.766
To remove the most recent sin,
here are your options:

12:13.799 --> 12:15.968
One, take responsibility.

12:17.035 --> 12:18.504
End of options.

12:19.504 --> 12:20.740
Okay.

12:22.808 --> 12:25.144
- [glove compartment opens]
- [rustling]

12:29.414 --> 12:30.449
Thanks, God.

12:30.482 --> 12:32.384
[chiming]
You're welcome, Claire.

13:03.949 --> 13:05.117
[moans softly]

13:09.955 --> 13:12.925
[chiming]
New update available.

13:12.958 --> 13:15.561
New features--
future foresight,

13:15.594 --> 13:20.032
communication with up to
seven deceased relatives
and wireless compatibility.

13:20.065 --> 13:22.301
To update overnight,
say "yes" at the tone.

13:22.334 --> 13:24.069
- [chimes]
- Yes.

13:30.008 --> 13:33.012
♪♪

14:05.477 --> 14:08.380
So, Brian, you gonna
buy me dinner first,

14:08.413 --> 14:11.016
or we just gonna
get right to it?
[soft chuckle]

14:11.049 --> 14:15.254
Charlie, tell me, what do you
know about sex? Huh?

14:15.287 --> 14:18.557
It's the motion of the ocean
that matters the most.

14:18.590 --> 14:20.993
Am I right?

14:21.026 --> 14:24.129
- Yeah, you're right.
- [chuckles]

14:24.162 --> 14:26.365
Are we doing
a full body scan again?

14:26.398 --> 14:31.203
- We did one last week.
- Yeah, just one more.

14:31.236 --> 14:34.539
Is it because of my highbrow
sense of humor

14:34.572 --> 14:37.042
that's upsetting people?

14:37.075 --> 14:39.578
Everyone's getting
checked again
before the holidays.

14:39.611 --> 14:42.314
Right. The holidays.

14:44.349 --> 14:48.353
You spending them
with someone special?

14:48.386 --> 14:51.123
No, not really.

14:51.156 --> 14:53.091
You know, you should
just spend them here.

14:53.124 --> 14:55.227
I'm great company.

14:55.260 --> 14:58.697
Yeah, you're right.
That does sound nice,
actually.

14:58.730 --> 15:02.501
Would it be too much trouble
to dress up as Santa Claus?

15:02.534 --> 15:05.103
Whatever you want,
Charlie.

15:05.136 --> 15:07.039
- Let me help you.
- Oh, come on, Brian.

15:07.072 --> 15:09.341
I never had Santa
as a child.

15:09.374 --> 15:12.912
- You never were a child.
- Oh, good point.

15:15.647 --> 15:18.383
Am I doing something wrong,
Brian?

15:18.416 --> 15:21.153
You're doing
everything wrong.

15:21.186 --> 15:22.154
[scoffs]

15:23.154 --> 15:24.290
Don't hold back.

15:26.124 --> 15:28.493
I'm serious, though.

15:28.526 --> 15:32.364
I've been in this place
for two months to the day.

15:32.397 --> 15:36.402
I've never met anybody
that was here
past the two-month mark.

15:40.038 --> 15:41.273
You know, it would be nice

15:41.306 --> 15:45.377
if somebody young
took me home that got me.

15:45.410 --> 15:46.645
You know, like you.

15:48.246 --> 15:50.215
You can do
much better than me.

15:50.248 --> 15:51.550
Better?

15:52.550 --> 15:55.988
I don't wanna seem
needy, Brian.

15:56.021 --> 15:58.757
But we get along great.
You're my friend.

15:58.790 --> 16:00.092
Trust me,
you can do better.

16:00.125 --> 16:01.627
You're my friend,
though, right?

16:03.395 --> 16:05.597
Of course, Charlie,
I'm your friend.

16:08.166 --> 16:09.401
Good.

16:12.437 --> 16:14.072
Okay, lie down.

16:14.105 --> 16:17.042
We have this new machine.

16:18.043 --> 16:19.278
So lie down.

16:23.615 --> 16:25.517
And you need
to close your eyes.

16:25.550 --> 16:28.420
Okay.

16:28.453 --> 16:31.189
Can you play some music?

16:31.222 --> 16:33.058
Sure.

16:33.091 --> 16:34.593
[music playing]

16:34.626 --> 16:37.363
Can you turn it up a bit?
I love that song.

16:38.763 --> 16:39.798
Sure, buddy.

16:39.831 --> 16:42.468
[jazz music playing]

16:54.779 --> 16:56.782
[crushing]

17:06.458 --> 17:07.393
[music stops]

17:24.642 --> 17:27.646
♪♪

17:39.390 --> 17:41.827
[thunder rumbles softly]

17:59.811 --> 18:01.413
God?

18:13.491 --> 18:14.493
God?

18:24.402 --> 18:25.504
God!

18:29.207 --> 18:30.309
Wake up.

18:37.815 --> 18:41.653
Fuck, fuck, fuck,
fuck, fuck, fuck, fuck.

18:43.755 --> 18:45.357
God?

18:46.224 --> 18:48.293
[woman on phone]
God 2.0 customer service.

18:48.326 --> 18:51.196
Please hold for the next
available operator.

18:51.229 --> 18:52.898
[hold music playing]

18:59.370 --> 19:00.539
[exhales]

19:03.408 --> 19:04.343
Oh!

19:05.643 --> 19:07.246
[sighs]

19:08.980 --> 19:10.815
[man on phone]
God 2.0 customer service.

19:10.848 --> 19:12.617
This phone call
may be recorded.

19:12.650 --> 19:15.620
Please state your name
and product serial number.

19:15.653 --> 19:18.957
Hi, my name is Claire Larry,

19:18.990 --> 19:21.793
and how do I find
the serial number?

19:21.826 --> 19:22.961
Can you request it from God?

19:22.994 --> 19:26.398
I can't.
He's not there.

19:26.431 --> 19:28.466
Oh, did you
recently do the update?

19:28.499 --> 19:30.735
- Yeah.
- Ooh, well, that's not good.

19:30.768 --> 19:32.804
- Why, what does that mean?
- Well, we've been having

19:32.837 --> 19:35.473
some technical issues
with that since the storm.

19:35.506 --> 19:37.509
I'm afraid I can't help you
over the phone, Clark.

19:37.542 --> 19:41.746
Um, my name's Claire.
And my last name is Larry.

19:41.779 --> 19:44.316
Oh, okay, Larry.
I think the easiest way

19:44.349 --> 19:46.518
is to make an appointment
with the Holy Genius Bar.

19:46.551 --> 19:49.555
♪♪

19:55.593 --> 19:58.597
["Heaven On Earth Remix"
by Summer Dregs, Johnny Balik
and Swayyvo playing]

20:02.000 --> 20:03.468
What took you so long
to ask me out?

20:04.736 --> 20:06.838
Mm, I don't know.

20:06.871 --> 20:08.406
Just thought you
wouldn't be into it.

20:08.439 --> 20:10.442
I never said I was.

20:14.879 --> 20:16.948
- [Ben] Hey, baby.
- [laughing]

20:16.981 --> 20:18.783
Say hi to the camera.

20:18.816 --> 20:19.818
Hi.

20:21.019 --> 20:23.321
What?
What should I do?

20:23.354 --> 20:26.558
Um, whatever
your heart desires.

20:26.591 --> 20:29.828
- Um, smoke rings.
- Oh, you can do smoke rings?

20:29.861 --> 20:31.363
- Mm-hmm.
- Prove it.

20:32.397 --> 20:33.798
[coughing]

20:33.831 --> 20:36.001
[laughing]

20:36.034 --> 20:39.371
Sick smoke rings, Anna.

20:39.404 --> 20:41.406
They say perfect circles
don't exist,

20:41.439 --> 20:43.708
- but you just
proved them wrong, baby.
- Fuck. [coughs]

20:43.741 --> 20:46.745
By the way, totally worth
you looking a little gross.

20:46.778 --> 20:50.582
I look gross.
Do I look gross?

20:50.615 --> 20:52.818
- You're so beautiful.
- You're the worst.

20:54.519 --> 20:56.255
Okay, stop.

21:07.432 --> 21:08.433
[Ben]
Fuck.

21:08.466 --> 21:09.334
[tires screech]

21:28.920 --> 21:31.923
♪♪

21:54.412 --> 21:55.514
[chuckles]

21:57.782 --> 21:58.817
[Ben grumbles]

21:59.817 --> 22:00.819
You're still here.

22:07.658 --> 22:08.760
[grunting]

22:14.132 --> 22:15.667
Stop staring at me.

22:24.976 --> 22:26.111
[whistling]

22:28.179 --> 22:29.715
[phone vibrating]

22:34.519 --> 22:36.421
[sighs]
What the hell?

22:40.558 --> 22:41.626
[scoffs]
Come on.

22:41.659 --> 22:43.662
[phone continues vibrating]

22:47.799 --> 22:50.101
- Hello?
- [Ben] Hey,
you on your way?

22:50.134 --> 22:52.404
Yeah, I'm on my way,
you creep.

22:52.437 --> 22:54.072
Suffocating me already.
Jesus.

22:54.105 --> 22:56.474
- You know that's why
you love me.
- Wait, wait, do you have wine?

22:56.507 --> 22:57.909
Yes, I got a bottle
of red right here.

22:57.942 --> 22:59.811
- Okay, I'll see you in five.
- Okay, bye.

23:04.749 --> 23:07.753
♪♪

23:11.155 --> 23:12.724
[panting]

23:23.000 --> 23:24.803
[David] God...

23:26.804 --> 23:29.908
if you can hear me...
right now...

23:31.142 --> 23:32.511
I'd, uh...

23:33.511 --> 23:34.613
I really, uh...

23:35.847 --> 23:38.016
I don't know.
Shit.

23:38.883 --> 23:40.919
Okay, all right,
I'm sorry, sorry, sorry.

23:40.952 --> 23:41.987
Let me start again.

23:46.224 --> 23:47.559
God?!

23:50.895 --> 23:53.998
I-I never asked you
for anything.

23:54.031 --> 23:55.100
Uh...

23:56.167 --> 23:58.570
I've never even
spoken to you.

23:59.904 --> 24:01.706
Huh. I always figured

24:01.739 --> 24:04.609
the universe would,
you know,

24:04.642 --> 24:08.213
lead me to wherever
I needed to be.

24:08.246 --> 24:11.883
But, uh, I don't think
this is the right way.

24:11.916 --> 24:14.152
- [nervous chuckle]
- [Eva] Recalculating route.

24:14.185 --> 24:16.120
Insert new destination.

24:16.153 --> 24:19.191
Not now, Eva.
Jesus!

24:22.260 --> 24:24.529
All right, well,
what's going on?

24:25.696 --> 24:26.931
I mean, what am I--

24:26.964 --> 24:28.533
What are we doing here, huh?

24:28.566 --> 24:31.769
What-what's the lesson here?

24:31.802 --> 24:35.106
What, that I'm selfish?
I already knew that.

24:35.139 --> 24:37.843
I mean, like,
what, do I look
like father material?

24:40.811 --> 24:43.848
I mean, there's people
down there fucking.

24:43.881 --> 24:47.585
They're fucking and they're
murdering each other,
and you're coming after me?

24:47.618 --> 24:49.754
You better get
your priorities
straight, buster.

24:51.556 --> 24:52.891
I mean, if you think
I deserve this...

24:54.191 --> 24:58.096
well, maybe you should
have made me better.

24:58.129 --> 25:01.766
I mean, this might
actually be your fault.

25:01.799 --> 25:04.269
[scoffs] I mean, as far
as fathers go,

25:04.302 --> 25:05.871
you're not very good either!

25:07.071 --> 25:08.840
Either.

25:08.873 --> 25:10.208
Shit.

25:10.241 --> 25:11.243
[sighs]

25:17.882 --> 25:19.217
[panting]

25:35.700 --> 25:37.802
I look gross?

25:37.835 --> 25:38.837
Do I look gross?

25:41.038 --> 25:43.141
Is it bad?

25:43.174 --> 25:44.976
You look beautiful.

25:45.009 --> 25:46.444
[bleating]

25:46.477 --> 25:49.247
- Sorry, it comes out
every once in a while.
- That was not a goat.

25:49.280 --> 25:52.817
[clears throat]
That wasn't a goat?
What was it then?

25:52.850 --> 25:54.152
That was a sheep.

25:54.185 --> 25:56.020
Oh, you really know
your farm animals.

25:56.053 --> 26:00.124
- [chuckles]
- Um, okay, what does
a goat sound like?

26:00.157 --> 26:01.860
Do it for me.

26:03.160 --> 26:05.296
Ba-ha-ha.
[laughing]

26:05.329 --> 26:08.666
That's a donkey,
that is not a goat at all.

26:08.699 --> 26:12.704
- By the way,
I just want to say...
- What?

26:12.737 --> 26:15.239
I'm sorry
for getting you a burger.

26:15.272 --> 26:17.576
- Why are you sorry for--
- Well, I should have
gotten you hay.

26:22.279 --> 26:25.283
♪♪

26:42.033 --> 26:43.735
Hey.

26:43.768 --> 26:45.870
Hey, what's going on?

26:45.903 --> 26:47.071
Come here.

26:47.104 --> 26:50.241
[Anna] This thing...
he follows me.

26:50.274 --> 26:53.811
- Hey, it's okay.
- [sighs] I see it
all the time.

26:53.844 --> 26:54.946
It's gonna be okay.

26:54.979 --> 26:56.881
[crickets chirping]

27:08.325 --> 27:09.628
[faucet runs]

27:12.163 --> 27:13.898
[swishing]

27:13.931 --> 27:15.099
[spits]

27:15.132 --> 27:17.135
[clattering in distance]

27:21.305 --> 27:24.309
♪♪

28:15.159 --> 28:16.394
[grunts]

28:18.996 --> 28:20.065
[shuddering]

28:27.438 --> 28:29.441
[yelling]

28:36.347 --> 28:37.382
[grunts]

28:39.784 --> 28:42.220
[crying]

28:54.064 --> 28:55.266
I have an appointment.

28:56.534 --> 28:57.936
Yeah, I know.

29:00.805 --> 29:01.973
[computer chiming]

29:08.045 --> 29:09.914
- So?
- Mm...

29:13.350 --> 29:14.385
Okay, so here's
the problem.

29:14.418 --> 29:16.954
Never update
without doing
a manual restart.

29:16.987 --> 29:18.222
Oh, no, that's not true.
He just said,

29:18.255 --> 29:20.558
"Say yes at the tone,"
and then he died.

29:20.591 --> 29:23.094
Did you hold down the button
till God shut down
and restarted?

29:25.162 --> 29:28.132
- No.
- [whispers] Okay then.

29:28.165 --> 29:30.368
- [chiming]
- [normal voice] Oh, I see
you pay for the cloud monthly

29:30.401 --> 29:33.304
so at least you have a backup
of your good deeds and sins.

29:35.139 --> 29:36.441
Can you see my sins?

29:38.242 --> 29:39.511
You want me to?

29:40.511 --> 29:42.814
Okay, so moving on.

29:42.847 --> 29:44.315
You back up every day, right?

29:44.348 --> 29:47.018
Yeah, no, no,
I don't, sometimes, maybe.

29:47.051 --> 29:50.521
Okay, what's going to happen
is we can offer you a discount
on a new system.

29:50.554 --> 29:52.290
How long have you been
with your current God?

29:53.891 --> 29:56.093
- Four years.
- Wow.

29:56.126 --> 29:58.596
Okay, you're supposed
to renew your faith
every 18 months.

29:58.629 --> 30:00.531
- No, you're not.
- Yeah.

30:00.564 --> 30:01.933
I'm surprised
he stayed with you
this long.

30:06.070 --> 30:07.939
Just give me
a new model then.

30:07.972 --> 30:08.940
[typing]

30:11.008 --> 30:12.410
He'll be shipped to you
by tomorrow.

30:12.443 --> 30:13.945
How am I gonna pray?

30:16.247 --> 30:18.883
You'll have to do it
manually.

30:28.259 --> 30:29.961
God...

30:35.165 --> 30:37.602
are you there?

30:42.206 --> 30:43.441
Hello?

30:47.378 --> 30:49.247
God?

30:49.280 --> 30:51.216
This is so stupid.

30:56.921 --> 30:58.923
Where are your parents?

31:09.133 --> 31:11.469
God... Oh, shit.

31:12.703 --> 31:14.572
[man on phone]
God 2.0 customer service.

31:14.605 --> 31:16.374
This phone call
may be recorded.

31:16.407 --> 31:18.075
So, I've been
trying to pray manually

31:18.108 --> 31:21.245
and, uh, nobody's answering.

31:21.278 --> 31:25.349
So, I feel... kind of stupid,

31:25.382 --> 31:30.121
and I was just wondering
if maybe...

31:30.154 --> 31:35.593
you could talk back to me
while I do it?

31:35.626 --> 31:38.129
Ma'am, we do not provide
spiritual responses

31:38.162 --> 31:40.364
to God 2.0 customers
over the phone.

31:40.397 --> 31:43.167
I can sign you up
for an automated
hotline service

31:43.200 --> 31:45.469
for just a $199 per mont.

31:45.502 --> 31:49.206
No, no, uh,
of course you don't.

31:49.239 --> 31:50.608
That's-- Just--
I actually was asking

31:50.641 --> 31:52.443
just if you could
maybe do just quick response,

31:52.476 --> 31:54.378
like, um,
just an inspirational quote,

31:54.411 --> 31:58.582
you know, "Best preparation
for tomorrow is..."

31:58.615 --> 32:02.053
Or something about today
or just getting through.

32:02.086 --> 32:03.554
Uh, n.

32:06.256 --> 32:07.591
I'm sorry, ma'a.

32:07.624 --> 32:09.627
Is there anything else
I can help you with?

32:11.528 --> 32:13.664
Hell?

32:13.697 --> 32:15.667
Hello, ma'a?

32:17.067 --> 32:18.202
[thunder cracks]

32:19.536 --> 32:22.540
♪♪

33:07.751 --> 33:09.387
[God 2.0] Buenos días, Larry.

33:09.420 --> 33:12.656
- Oh, God.
- ¿Inglés?

33:12.689 --> 33:16.093
- Sí, sí, inglés.
- Good morning, Larry!

33:16.126 --> 33:19.697
Congratulations
for choosing God 2.0!
New and improved!

33:19.730 --> 33:22.800
Wireless, waterproof,
non-flammable
and simply indestructible.

33:22.833 --> 33:24.702
Made exclusively
from recycled bots,

33:24.735 --> 33:28.039
God 2.0 is saving you
and the planet.

33:28.072 --> 33:30.207
Larry, come on down
to Mattress Deluxe

33:30.240 --> 33:33.077
where we have
thousands of mattresses
at wholesale prices!

33:33.110 --> 33:35.246
Jesus fucking Christ.

33:35.279 --> 33:38.749
You used the Lord's
name in vain.
One sin recorded.

33:38.782 --> 33:40.785
You having trouble
gaining muscle mass?

33:40.818 --> 33:42.220
- No.
- Of course you do!

33:42.253 --> 33:45.089
Trainers are going
out of business
because of protein water.

33:45.122 --> 33:47.758
Make it stop.
Uh, stop ads, please.

33:47.791 --> 33:51.295
To stop advertisements,
sign up for Premium God 2.0.

33:51.328 --> 33:54.832
- [sighs]
- To roll your eyes at God
is a sign of contempt.

33:54.865 --> 33:56.267
One sin recorded.

33:56.300 --> 33:59.437
- Can you see me?
- Yes, I see everything.

33:59.470 --> 34:02.473
The new God 2.0 is equipped
with visual sensor technology.

34:04.308 --> 34:07.812
- Shit.
- Swearing.
One sin recorded.

34:07.845 --> 34:10.181
- Turn off.
- [chiming]

34:10.214 --> 34:13.217
The new God 2.0
has an eternal battery life,

34:13.250 --> 34:15.319
and cannot be powered down.

34:15.352 --> 34:17.088
Forever in your presence.

34:17.121 --> 34:21.292
Making you
a better person, always.

34:21.325 --> 34:24.862
♪♪

34:24.895 --> 34:27.865
No, no, no, no, no!
[screams]

34:27.898 --> 34:29.533
[car alarm blaring]

34:29.566 --> 34:32.570
♪♪

34:57.528 --> 34:59.864
[Nina] You know, I haven't
been back to this area
since I was a kid.

35:02.299 --> 35:03.834
There was a slight incident.

35:03.867 --> 35:08.106
There was some fireworks
and a friend's robot.

35:09.773 --> 35:10.875
What happened?

35:14.811 --> 35:16.547
I might have blown it up.

35:16.580 --> 35:17.882
[both laughing]

35:19.917 --> 35:21.619
And I was never invited back,
you know,

35:21.652 --> 35:22.920
so I'm feeling
the pressure.

35:22.954 --> 35:25.456
Okay, probably best
not to mention that
at dinner tonight.

35:25.489 --> 35:26.757
No, you don't think
they'd like that?

35:26.790 --> 35:28.592
- Probably not.
- Probably not.

35:28.625 --> 35:30.394
I thought it'd make me
a bit dangerous,
but whatever.

35:30.427 --> 35:33.364
- I get it. I get it.
- [laughing]

35:33.397 --> 35:36.333
But I'm serious,
I'm really nervous.

35:36.366 --> 35:40.271
You know, I've never been
with someone of your kind.

35:40.304 --> 35:42.773
What, someone so privileged,
and so self-loathing?

35:42.806 --> 35:45.442
- Yeah, all my favorite parts
about you.
- Hmm.

35:45.475 --> 35:47.444
I was actually
having some doubts

35:47.477 --> 35:50.281
- about you and I.
- Hey! That's mean.

35:50.314 --> 35:52.383
I think it's a little odd

35:52.416 --> 35:55.819
that you would use
my childhood sippy cup
as an ashtray.

35:55.852 --> 35:58.389
You-- The childhood
sippy cup is odd.

35:58.422 --> 36:00.357
- Who gave you the sippy cup?
- My mom.

36:00.390 --> 36:02.927
It's exactly for that reason

36:02.960 --> 36:05.563
I find the sippy cup
a little bit weird.

36:05.596 --> 36:08.465
- It's sentimental.
- Do you not think
that that's a reminder

36:08.498 --> 36:12.603
of what it was like
to attach to the last...
[laughs]

36:12.636 --> 36:17.541
I'm going to say it,
nipple-like thing
in your life?

36:17.574 --> 36:18.943
[both laughing]

36:20.711 --> 36:22.413
No, seriously.
Seriously.

36:22.446 --> 36:24.549
Is she-- is she going
to hate me?

36:25.816 --> 36:26.784
Yeah.

36:28.752 --> 36:30.688
- Really?
- Hm.

36:30.721 --> 36:32.924
- Is she really mean?
- Yeah.

36:34.291 --> 36:36.393
- [laughs]
- Well, I'm really great.

36:36.426 --> 36:38.562
So I'm going
to make this amazing.

36:38.595 --> 36:39.764
She's going to love me.
Watch this.

36:41.298 --> 36:44.969
So strange.
What a strange... house

36:45.002 --> 36:47.571
[scoffs] Oh, is that--
is that--

36:47.604 --> 36:49.306
Do you have a dog?
Is that--?

36:49.339 --> 36:51.875
- [Liam] No.
- Do you think that's
something on my shoe?

36:51.908 --> 36:55.246
- Look-- Do you think
that's dog poo?
- No, you look fine.

36:55.279 --> 36:58.616
I cannot go into your house
smelling like dog shit.

36:58.649 --> 37:01.919
- Yeah.
- That's just a no-go.

37:01.952 --> 37:04.255
This is so embarrassing.
Are you sure?

37:04.288 --> 37:06.357
- Yeah, you're fine.
- Oh, I smell like poo.

37:06.390 --> 37:08.525
- [door unlocks, whirs]
- Ooh! The door opened.

37:08.558 --> 37:10.394
- Where's your mom?
- [Dora] Hello, darling!

37:10.427 --> 37:11.629
Come on in.

37:11.662 --> 37:14.265
Your father and sister
are in the game room.

37:14.298 --> 37:15.566
Oh, God.

37:15.599 --> 37:18.603
♪♪

37:19.836 --> 37:21.672
[indistinct chatter]

37:22.739 --> 37:26.343
- [Ron] If you wanna
watch the master.
- That's what I rolled.

37:26.376 --> 37:27.945
See how it goes.

37:27.978 --> 37:31.315
[Olivia] Take a nap,
he takes forever.

37:31.348 --> 37:32.583
Yeah, thank you.

37:32.616 --> 37:34.285
[indistinct chatter]

37:34.318 --> 37:35.386
Watch, guys. Watch, guys.

37:35.419 --> 37:36.687
[dice rattle]

37:36.720 --> 37:38.355
- Yeah!
- [Olivia] No!

37:38.388 --> 37:39.723
Oh, I'm so pumped.

37:39.756 --> 37:41.659
- Wow.
- So gonna pl--
I'm killing on this.

37:41.692 --> 37:43.694
Looks like you built
a water park instead, Dad.

37:43.727 --> 37:45.462
Don't tell your mother.

37:45.495 --> 37:47.931
[Dora] Ron, I think
that's enough now.

37:47.964 --> 37:50.467
[Ron] We should never
have installed
a home optics system.

37:50.500 --> 37:53.470
Word of advice.
Keep the home optic stuff
to the bedroom,

37:53.503 --> 37:55.673
- you don't need it
for the whole house.
- [Olivia] Eww, Dad. Stop.

37:55.706 --> 37:58.342
[Ron] No, most accidents
happen in the bedroom.

37:58.375 --> 38:01.345
So, you finally admit
that Olivia is an accident?

38:01.378 --> 38:03.414
You're an accident, Liam.

38:03.447 --> 38:04.548
Except you happened
in the living room.

38:06.083 --> 38:08.519
- [Olivia] Wait, where?
- Ay, ay, ay.

38:08.552 --> 38:09.754
[Ron]
Right, your go.

38:10.787 --> 38:12.490
No cheating
like your sister.

38:13.824 --> 38:15.359
- [Olivia] Yes!
- [Ron] Watch and weep.

38:16.493 --> 38:20.631
[Nina] Well, apparently
mission control
lost contact with him.

38:20.664 --> 38:23.834
[Dora scoffs]
You'd think they'd just
get robots to do it by now.

38:23.867 --> 38:25.869
Why would anybody
go up there?

38:25.902 --> 38:29.040
Sometimes you
just need some space.

38:30.507 --> 38:32.609
Oh, I'm so sorry.
I'm so sorry.

38:32.642 --> 38:36.380
Nina, let him do it.
That's what he's
programmed for.

38:36.413 --> 38:37.815
[Ron] We just adopted him
a couple of days ago.

38:39.149 --> 38:42.553
[Dora] We only rescue.
It's the best thing to do.

38:42.586 --> 38:43.921
Why don't they rescue
the space guy?

38:43.954 --> 38:46.924
The news said
that rescue mission
is impossible.

38:46.957 --> 38:49.660
I wonder
what he's thinking about.

38:49.693 --> 38:52.363
Floating up there,
all by himself.

38:53.830 --> 38:56.934
[Ron]
Probably... nothing.

38:56.967 --> 38:58.635
I think that that's
the best part,

38:58.668 --> 39:00.771
you can just shut off
the old computer.

39:00.804 --> 39:02.873
So you wouldn't be
thinking about me then, Ron?

39:02.906 --> 39:04.675
Well, of course, hon.

39:04.708 --> 39:09.079
By "nothing", I meant
nothing else but you.

39:09.112 --> 39:10.514
- Good save.
- Thanks.

39:10.547 --> 39:11.882
No, I'm not buying it, Liam.

39:11.915 --> 39:14.418
[Ron scoffs] I can't even
float alone through space

39:14.451 --> 39:15.786
without her telling me
what to do.

39:17.888 --> 39:19.456
You know,
I think there's, uh,

39:19.489 --> 39:22.159
something poetic about floating
through space like that.

39:22.192 --> 39:23.694
[Nina] Why?

39:23.727 --> 39:25.996
Well, 'cause you know
how it's gonna end.

39:26.029 --> 39:27.898
What's poetic about dying?

39:30.434 --> 39:31.668
Everything.

39:31.701 --> 39:33.804
It's so primitive to think

39:33.837 --> 39:35.639
that the only way
a life has meaning

39:35.672 --> 39:37.641
is if you know
it's going to end.

39:37.674 --> 39:39.610
Um, not really, Mom.

39:39.643 --> 39:42.546
I mean, not everyone
is blessed with
the luxury of eternal life.

39:42.579 --> 39:44.181
Oh, I'm sorry.

39:44.214 --> 39:47.718
Should we be ashamed
of how blessed we are?

39:47.751 --> 39:49.453
No, I just don't think

39:49.486 --> 39:50.855
that we should rub it in
our guest's face.

39:52.155 --> 39:53.690
Oh.

39:53.723 --> 39:55.025
I apologize, Nina.

39:55.058 --> 39:57.728
I didn't mean to make you
feel uncomfortable.

39:57.761 --> 40:00.097
Oh... [chuckles]
Don't worry, I'm--

40:00.130 --> 40:02.833
I'm not uncomfortable
at all.

40:02.866 --> 40:04.501
I actually like being mortal.

40:04.534 --> 40:07.104
See, not everyone
is dying not to die.

40:07.137 --> 40:10.641
Sure. But I would assume
that given the choice,

40:10.674 --> 40:13.677
anyone with a sane mind
would choose to go on living.

40:13.710 --> 40:15.546
Well, I didn't have a choice.

40:17.647 --> 40:20.818
I wasn't born
in the same tier group
you were,

40:20.851 --> 40:22.820
so I didn't get to choose.

40:23.887 --> 40:25.489
But I'm okay with that.

40:27.123 --> 40:30.027
But don't you feel like
you're missing out
on so much time?

40:30.060 --> 40:33.664
Well, I mean, time
just becomes more precious.

40:36.132 --> 40:38.735
There we go
with the primitive thinking.

40:38.768 --> 40:41.071
What's your issue?

40:41.104 --> 40:43.040
We, as a family,

40:43.073 --> 40:45.108
of course we're
really excited about Nina.

40:45.141 --> 40:48.645
She's really lovely.

40:48.678 --> 40:52.149
- But, we do have some--
- [Dora] Concerns.

40:52.182 --> 40:56.753
- Concerns, yes.
- We have some concerns.

40:56.786 --> 40:58.989
All right, I mean,
I'd love to hear them.

41:05.161 --> 41:07.264
None? Nothing?

41:07.297 --> 41:10.601
Mom and Dad think
you dating a mortal
is a waste of time.

41:10.634 --> 41:12.970
I never said it
in those words.

41:13.003 --> 41:15.606
Look, Nina, I-I think
you're very lovely.

41:15.639 --> 41:19.276
But we have to be
realistic here.

41:19.309 --> 41:21.745
Well, I mean,

41:21.778 --> 41:25.115
please, do tell us
your ultra-modern take
on this, uh...

41:27.017 --> 41:28.652
It's a big sacrifice

41:28.685 --> 41:31.755
to waste time on something
that's going to end.

41:31.788 --> 41:36.093
And especially when that end
is so heartbreaking.

41:36.126 --> 41:37.694
No offense, Nina.

41:37.727 --> 41:39.563
Oh, none taken.

41:39.596 --> 41:42.833
She's going to get sick,
and then she will die.

41:42.866 --> 41:45.769
Do you really need to be
around there for that, Liam?

41:47.170 --> 41:48.605
Yeah.

41:48.638 --> 41:49.973
I love this woman,

41:50.006 --> 41:52.810
so I want to spend
all the time I can with her.

41:54.177 --> 41:56.146
Don't you see
what you're doing, Nina?

41:56.179 --> 41:58.148
- Hold on.
- I'm not doing anything.

41:58.181 --> 42:00.784
You're dragging him
down with you.

42:00.817 --> 42:03.053
Why can't you find someone
of your own kind?

42:03.086 --> 42:05.189
[chuckles] You know, uh...

42:06.023 --> 42:09.326
I wasn't planning
on telling you guys today.

42:09.359 --> 42:10.661
But... [scoffs]

42:13.029 --> 42:15.899
I've decided to die naturally
with Nina.

42:15.932 --> 42:18.702
Excuse me?

42:18.735 --> 42:19.736
I'm turning it off.

42:19.769 --> 42:22.873
[Dora scoffs]
I don't think so.

42:22.906 --> 42:26.810
- What?
- I don't wanna live
forever without you.

42:26.843 --> 42:29.179
[Dora] That's crazy talk.

42:29.212 --> 42:31.782
Why, just spend time
with her then.

42:31.815 --> 42:34.851
- Don't kill yourself over it.
- I'm not killing myself.

42:34.884 --> 42:37.588
Look, have your fun now,

42:37.621 --> 42:40.190
and then, when she dies,
do a memory reset.

42:40.223 --> 42:42.859
Delete her.

42:42.892 --> 42:44.628
That is so cold.

42:44.661 --> 42:46.363
- [Ron] I'm a romantic too.
- [chuckles]

42:46.396 --> 42:49.333
You've got so much more time
and accomplishments
ahead of you.

42:52.302 --> 42:55.773
So I can what? Hmm?
Make more money?

42:57.107 --> 42:58.642
Then what?
Get another hobby?

42:58.675 --> 43:00.811
Learn another language
I'm never gonna use?

43:00.844 --> 43:04.047
When you can do
anything you want tomorrow,

43:04.080 --> 43:05.783
today doesn't really matter.

43:07.884 --> 43:09.687
I made my decision.

43:11.988 --> 43:13.924
[Dora] You know
you can't reverse this.

43:13.957 --> 43:18.729
- Once you switch it off...
- [Ron] Mm.

43:18.762 --> 43:21.632
...you'll be just like them,
like her.

43:24.734 --> 43:27.971
You'll age,
you'll get sick
and then...

43:28.004 --> 43:31.775
Liam, you know, I'd never
ask you to do this for me.

43:31.808 --> 43:33.143
It's my choice.

43:34.344 --> 43:36.046
[Dora] I'm not gonna
let this happen.

43:36.079 --> 43:39.249
Absolutely no way.

43:40.049 --> 43:43.654
Well, you know,
I think it's about time
I went for a cigarette.

